Env.Page.Title = Security

Env.Help.Text << EOM
In the <b>Encryption</b> section, you can choose the encryption system to be used by you wireless network. Setting a encryption system is strongly advised. Furthermore, the encryption system should be chosen depending on your Wifi equipments.
<br /><br />Depending on the radio mode chosen, some encryption systems might not be available. The <b>11n</b> radio mode only works with <b>WPA2 Personal (PSK)</b>, <b>11b/g/n</b> only with <b>WPA Personal (PSK)</b> and/or <b>WPA2 Personal (PSK)</b> and <b>11b/g</b> works with all the encryption systems.<br/><br/>For security reasons, it is advisable to focus on WPA2.<br/> For compatibility reasons, it is advisable to use a key type TKIP with WPA.
<br/><br/>In the <b>Wifi Protected Setup (WPS)</b> section, you can enable the WPS service. This service allows to easily connect a compatible Wifi device to your wireless network. This mode is only enabled with WPA or WPA2 encryption.
<br/><br/>3 WPS pairing methods are possible :
<ul>
    <li>WPS button : Use this method if your wireless equipment requires you to press the WPS button on your access point. The Wifi button on your <b > Box </ b> also allows you to start this method.</li>
    <li>Device PIN Code : Use this method if your wireless device has a PIN code and enter it in the field indicated.</li>
    <li>Box PIN Code : Use this method if your Wifi equipment requests a PIN code to the access point . A new code is generated each time this method is launched.</li>
</ul>
EOM

Env.Text.GenerateKey = Generate a key

